distribution.description:
Ectomycorrhizal data 
Created by:Josh Wasyliw
date:2020-03-12

Site = Site ID number;

Depth_Comb = Depth increments used for analysis (Top = 0–30 cm; Deep = 30–90 cm);

Age = Mean age of trees within stand (years);

Age_C = Age class (1 = 2–5 y; 2 = 12–16 y; 3 = 30–36 y; 4 = 65–76 y);

FRA = Fine root surface area of Pinus banksiana (cm2);

FRM = Fine root dry mass of Pinus banksiana (mg);

Distance = Count of distance EcM root tips observed in subsample;

Contact = Count of contact EcM root tips observed in subsample;

Uncolonized = Count of uncolonized root tips observed in subsample;

Deteriorated = Count of deteriorated root tips observed in subsample;

Root_tip_no = Estimated total number of root tips in sample (using WinRHIZO software);

Total_examined = Total number of root tips scored;

Dist_cm2 = Estimated number of distance tips per unit root surface area (cm2) – constant (0.001) added to permit statistical analysis

Leaf area and mass data
Created by:Josh Wasyliw;
date:2020-03-12;
Site = Site ID number;
Age = Mean age of trees within stand (years);
Age_C = Age class (Seedling = 2–5 y; Sapling = 12–16 y; Mid = 30–36 y; Old = 65–76 y);
Plot_area = Size of tree measurement plot (m2);
Leaf_mass = Dry mass of leaves (kg);
Leaf_area = Leaf area (m2);
LAI = Leaf area index: ratio of leaf surface area to unit ground surface area

Data used for the calculation of beta coefficients to describe vertical root distribution in a chronosequence of Pinus banksiana stands.
Created by: Josh Wasyliw;
Date: 2020-03-12;
Site = Site ID number;
Depth_cm = Sampling depth in cm;
Depth = Sample depth class;
Age = Mean age of trees within stand (years);
Age_C = Age class (1 = 2–5 y; 2 = 12–16 y; 3 = 30–36 y; 4 = 65–76 y);
TRA = Total fine root area (cm2);
Cumulative_TRA = Sum of fine root surface area from soil surface to a given depth (cm2);
Cumulative_Fraction = Cumulative root area at given soil depth / Total fine root area from 0–90 cm

Fine root measurements
Created by: Josh Wasyliw;
Date: 2020-03-12;
Site = Site ID number;
Core = Soil coring location within site;
Depth = Sample depth class in cm (A = 0–15; B = 15–30, C = 30–45, D = 45–60, E = 60–75, F = 75–90);
Depth_Comb = Depth increments used for analysis (Top = 0–30 cm; Deep = 30–90 cm);
Age = Mean age of trees within stand (years);
Age_C = Age class (1 = 2–5 y; 2 = 12–16 y; 3 = 30–36 y; 4 = 65–76 y);
FRA = Fine root surface area of Pinus banksiana (cm2);
FRM = Fine root dry mass of Pinus banksiana (mg);
*** FRA and FRM data were scaled by unit ground surface area for statistical analyses***;
soil core diameter = 7.62cm
